<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="UTF-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
		<title>ButchGamy - API documentation</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<h1>ButchGamy API documentation</h1>
		<p>
			<strong>Endpoint:</strong>
			<a href="{{ endpoint }}" target="_blank">{{ endpoint }}</a>
		</p>
		<p>All API calls require the following parameters:
			<ul>
				<li>apiKey: Your game's API key. You can find this in the game's edit page.</li>
				<li>user: The user identifier provided to you in the "user" GET parameter.</li>
				<li>salt: The salt provided to you in the "salt" GET parameter.</li>
				<li><em>No idea if this is correct, will have to ask how salting works</em></li>
			</ul>
		</p>
		<h2>Game Results</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>
					GET /result
					<p>Returns all results for the current user.</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					GET /result/last
					<p>Returns the most recently attained result for the current user.</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					POST /result
					<p>
						Posts a new result for the current user. Requires the following parameters:
						<ul>
							<li>score <em>(int)</em></li>
							<li>time <em>(int; in seconds)</em></li>
						</ul>
					</p>
				</li>
			</ul>
		<h2>Achievements</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>
					GET /achievement
					<p>Returns all achievements for the current user.</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					POST /achievement
					<p>
						Unlocks achievement for the current user; returns (value) as false if the achievement is already unlocked. Requires the following parameters:
						<ul>
							<li>name <em>(the achievement's unique identifier)</em></li>
							<li>description <em>(keep it snappy; max length 255)</em></li>
							<li>image <em>(as url; recommended 64x64)</em></li>
						</ul>
					</p>
				</li>
			</ul>
		<h2>Users</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>
					GET /user
					<p>Returns the username and profile picture (as URL) for the current user.</p>
				</li>
			</ul>
	</body>
</html>
